26/05/2005
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Interpol's annual general meeting started in Nicosia on Wednesday (25 May), attended by top European law enforcement agency officials. Issues related to international crisis co-ordination, combating human and drug trafficking and organised crime top the agenda of the three-day conference. On Wednesday, Interpol President Jackie Selebi called for enhanced preparedness to prevent and deal with new threats, such as a bioterrorism attack. (Kathimerini - 26/05/05) 
